"title": "5348: injustice, nature and source of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5348",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Characterised by deception, dishonesty and heartlessness, injustice is the oppression of the needy and the weak. Its origin is Satan and it works through the sinful hearts of men and women.\n <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:6\">PSA 64:6</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The nature of injustice</h2>\n<h3>Injustice seen in false accusation</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:19-Gen39:20\">GEN 39:19–39:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:8-1Kgs21:10\">1KI 21:8–21:10</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice seen in dishonesty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:14\">ISA 59:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:59-Matt26:61\">MAT 26:59–26:61</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:26-Acts24:27\">ACT 24:26–24:27</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice seen in pain inficted on the innocent</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16-Matt2:18\">MAT 2:16–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:3\">ACT 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:3\">ACT 23:3</a></p>\n<h3>Injustice seen in oppression of the poor, the needy and the helpless</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:11-Exod1:14\">EXO 1:11–1:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:11\">1SA 8:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:14\">2CH 10:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:13-Job31:14\">JOB 31:13–31:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:2\">PSA 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:8-Ps10:11\">PSA 10:8–10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:17-Ps105:18\">PSA 105:17–105:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:16\">PRO 22:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8\">ISA 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13\">JER 22:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11\">AMO 5:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:38-Mark12:40\">MRK 12:38–12:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4-Jas5:6\">JAS 5:4–5:6</a></p>\n<h2>The sources of injustice</h2>\n<h3>The devil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:10\">1JN 3:10</a></strong> <em>The word “devil” means “slanderer”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">JHN 8:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:9-2Thess2:11\">2TH 2:9–2:11</a> <em>The word “Satan” means “adversary”--the same person as the devil</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:14-Jas3:15\">JAS 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:13\">REV 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>The world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></strong> <em>“the world” here means society without God and hostile to him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:2\">EXO 23:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:4\">PSA 69:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:4-Prov31:5\">PRO 31:4–31:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:12\">EZK 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:11-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:11–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:18-John15:19\">JHN 15:18–15:19</a></p>\n<h3>Sinful hearts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:19\">MAT 15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:2\">PSA 140:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:13-Jer6:15\">JER 6:13–6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:2\">MIC 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:21\">GAL 5:19–5:21</a></p>",
